N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 933.1 - Purpose and Effect of Regulations

State Regulations
(a) The purpose of these regulations is to
effectuate the statutory provisions of Public Officers Law section 73(5), which
incorporates the provisions of section 1-c(j) of article 1-A of the Legislative

Law. (b) The effect of these
regulations is to supersede prior advisory opinions issued by predecessor
agencies to the Joint Commission on Public Ethics, including advisory opinion
nos. 94-16, 96-28, 97-03, and 08-01 to the extent they are inconsistent with
this Part. Notes
